&lt;p&gt;Our Client, University College London Hospital are looking for a Band 7 Women’s Health Physiotherapist to work full time, Monday to Friday 9-5 through Bank Partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a band 7 women’s health physiotherapist, the post-holder is responsible to assist in the daily operational management and service delivery, as well as supervision, education and training of the less experienced physiotherapy staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder is required to demonstrate highly developed time management &amp; prioritisation skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder is required to work collaboratively with all members of the WH multi-professional team, the Musculoskeletal Therapy Services Team and Service Managers on service development and quality assurance projects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to perform manual handling tasks such as highly specialised physical assessment and treatment skills,.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered for these roles, you will need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At least six months NHS experience desired&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HCPC registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the Bank you will benefit from:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First opportunity for work placements before agency staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive pay rates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A dedicated booking consultant available to assist with any queries and advise on suitable assignments tailored to you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electronic timesheet system with weekly payroll&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this role, please apply onloine today&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
